analyse.placeName: Old Town of Galle and its Fortifications, Galle Galle District Southern Province
analyse.bestReview: This is a very pleasant town to walk around.  Start at the clock tower and walk along the fortifications taking in the main bastion then on to the mosque and the lighthouse before going to see the Dutch Fort, Dutch Hospital & Dutch church. We had a pleasant lunch at the Rampart Hotel overlooking the sea.

analyse.placeName: Galle Fort, Galle Galle District Southern Province
analyse.bestReview: Fortification built by Portuguese in 16th century and extended by Dutch in 18th during the colonial era. Nice place to enjoy the sea Breeze with good sea view, but should do it during morning or evening time since afternoon sun can be scorching visiting at this place. analyse.bestReview: Martin Wickramainghe is a very important writer and person in the development of the modern Sri Lanka.
